# Data Rules

> Extends [root AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md). Auto-loaded when editing `*.schema.ts`, `*.repository.ts`, `migrations/*`.

## Database Selection

- New transactional collections MUST use Firestore Enterprise — MongoDB compat for Node.js/Mongoose (latest Mongoose version), Native mode for other languages or real-time listeners. [MUST]
- For analytics and reporting queries, use ClickHouse — not MongoDB or Memorystore.
- See [database-selection](references/database-selection.md) for full selection constraints (ClickHouse, OpenSearch, Memorystore, CloudSQL).

## Per-Database Rules

| Database | Rule File | Key Constraints |
|----------|-----------|-----------------|
| Firestore Enterprise | [firestore](references/firestore.md) | Dedicated database, `@platform-core/firestore` ORM |
| MongoDB / Mongoose | [mongodb](references/mongodb.md) | `locationId` scoping, typed schemas, compound indexes |
| Memorystore | [memorystore](references/memorystore.md) | TTL on all keys, SCAN not KEYS, key naming convention |
| Indexes | [indexes](references/indexes.md) | Liquibase for Mongo, Terraform for Firestore, autoIndex: false |
| Naming | [naming-conventions](references/naming-conventions.md) | Kebab-case, product-first, no env/team in names |
| Observability | [observability-orm](references/observability-orm.md) | All connections via `@platform-core/*` packages |

